'''Harry Dodgshun Bedford''' (31 August 1877 – 17 February 1918) was a New Zealand university academic and [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] for the City of [[Dunedin]].

==Biography==
===Early life===
Bedford was born in [[Leeds]], Yorkshire, England, in August 1877.<ref name="Bedford">{{DNZB |first = Michael |last = Gill |id = 3b21 |title = Bedford, Harry Dodgshun 1877-1918 |accessdate = 5 April 2011}}</ref> He later became a professor of [[history]] and [[economics]] at the [[University of Otago]] in Dunedin.

===Member of Parliament===
{{NZ parlbox header|nolist=true|align=left}}
{{NZ parlbox
 |start      = {{NZ election link year|1902}}
 |end        = 1905
 |term       = 15th
 |electorate = {{NZ electorate link|City of Dunedin}}
 |party      = Independent Liberal
}}
{{NZ parlbox allegiance
 |start      = 1905
 |party      = New Liberal Party (New Zealand)
